Johannesburg - Livingstone Etse Satekla better known by his stage name Stonebwoy was born in Ashaiman in the Greater Accra region of Ghana and began making music in his early school days. The multifaceted artist has received many awards and nominations ranging from Artist of the Year to Album of the Year. WATCH: One on One with Davido His sophomore album, Necessary Evil, was the recipient of three Ghana Music Awards from six nominations. In 2015 he became the second Ghanaian artist to win the Best International Act: Africa accolade at the BET awards, and was nominated for the same award in 2016. He sat down with eNCA's Mbali Langa to talk more about his music. eNCA